Which metric unit would be most appropriate for measuring the height of a classroom?
fields.explanation: The height of a classroom is typically a few meters tall, so meters is the most appropriate unit.

fields.question_text: Which metric unit would be most appropriate for measuring the distance around the school?
fields.explanation: The distance around a school perimeter is typically measured in kilometers.

fields.question_text: Which metric unit would be most appropriate for measuring the length of a pencil?
fields.explanation: A pencil is about 15-18 cm long, so centimeters is the most appropriate unit.

fields.question_text: Which metric unit would be most appropriate for measuring the width of a fingernail?
fields.explanation: A fingernail is about 1 cm wide, so millimeters would give the most precise measurement.

fields.question_text: Which metric unit would be most appropriate for measuring the distance between two cities?
fields.explanation: Distances between cities are measured in kilometers.

fields.question_text: Which metric unit would be most appropriate for measuring the length of a ruler?
fields.explanation: A ruler is 30 cm long, so centimeters is the appropriate unit.
